column28:
*Environment / Endpoint*

* *Endpoint:* {{POST https://api-s2.vault.musahm.com/api/documents/uploadDocument}}
* *Module:* Vault – Documents
* *Issue:* Intermittent HTTP 403 when uploading documents after the user has been using the app for a while

----

h3. Request Details

*Headers*

* {{Authorization: Bearer <JWT>}}
Example token (redacted in ticket, shared here for backend analysis):
{{eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..CiQlDYFLHfScNqRvqGY93T-BDcq7jqgdvtOfnMhXsB4}}
Payload highlights:
** {{Email}}: {{a.monir@runatetechnology.com}}
** {{UserType}}: {{Employee}}
** {{tenant_id}}: {{69c271966c1e58e6249bc65e}}
** {{user_id}}: {{69678cc60a65b73788236434}}
** {{CompanyId}}: {{232}}
** {{exp}}: {{1774474910}}
** {{IsAdmin}}: {{False}}

{quote}Note to backend: Please validate claims, roles, and any permission checks for this endpoint against this token structure.{quote}

*Body / Payload*

Multipart request with:

* {{file}}: (binary document)
* {{Status}}: {{Draft}}
* {{DocumentType}}: {{697f1a15036fb24402923363}}
* {{ParentId}}: {{69c29780142f5cff4847c836}}
* {{WorkspaceId}}: {{69c29780142f5cff4847c836}}
* {{Title}}: {{test0.1}}

----

h3. Observed Behaviour

* After the user has been logged in and using the app for some time, calling {{POST /api/documents/uploadDocument}} starts returning:
** *HTTP status:* {{403 Forbidden}}
* The same user and token were previously able to upload documents successfully (same endpoint and similar payload).
* No validation errors are returned in the body (backend returns only the 403 status).

----

h3. Expected Behaviour

* As long as the JWT is valid (not expired) and the user has permission to upload documents in the given *WorkspaceId/ParentId*, the endpoint should:
** Accept the request
** Create the document in *Draft* status
** Return a success status (e.g., {{200}} / {{201}}) instead of {{403}}.

----

h3. Hypothesis / Pointers for Backend

Please check:

# *Authorization/Policy checks*
#* Any change in role/permission mapping for:
#** {{UserType = Employee}}
#** {{CompanyId = 232}}
#** {{tenant_id = 69c271966c1e58e6249bc65e}}
#* Whether the combination of {{WorkspaceId}} + {{ParentId}} requires a role that this token no longer satisfies over time (e.g. cached permissions, tenant switching).
# *Token validation*
#* Whether there is any server‑side blacklisting / revocation / “single session” logic that might cause an otherwise valid token to start failing with {{403}} after a certain time or action.
#* Any clock skew / {{nbf}} and {{exp}} handling that might be mis‑calculated.
# *Resource‑level access*
#* Permission checks specific to:
#** {{DocumentType = 697f1a15036fb24402923363}}
#** {{WorkspaceId = 69c29780142f5cff4847c836}}
#** {{ParentId = 69c29780142f5cff4847c836}}
# *Logs*
#* Check server logs for this endpoint filtered by {{user_id = 69678cc60a65b73788236434}} and {{tenant_id = 69c271966c1e58e6249bc65e}} around the time of the 403 to see which authorization rule is failing.
